Question: Who is the most frequently appearing actor in our movie collection?

FROM actor a
JOIN film_actor fa ON a.actor_id = fa.actor_id
GROUP BY a.first_name, a.last_name
ORDER BY num_films DESC
LIMIT 1;
Expected SQL Query:
SELECT 
    a.actor_id, 
    a.first_name, 
    a.last_name, 
    COUNT(fa.film_id) AS film_count
FROM 
    actor a
    JOIN film_actor fa ON a.actor_id = fa.actor_id
GROUP BY 
    a.actor_id
ORDER BY 
    film_count DESC
LIMIT 1;

Question: Which five movie genres have made the most money overall?

    c.name AS genre, 
    SUM(p.amount) AS total_revenue
FROM 
    category c
JOIN film_category fc ON c.category_id = fc.category_id
JOIN film f ON fc.film_id = f.film_id
JOIN inventory i ON f.film_id = i.film_id
JOIN rental r ON i.inventory_id = r.inventory_id
JOIN payment p ON r.rental_id = p.rental_id

    c.name
ORDER BY 
    total_revenue DESC
LIMIT 5;

    JOIN payment p ON r.rental_id = p.rental_id

    gross_revenue DESC

Question: Which expensive-to-replace movies are also in the top five most popular categories?
Generated SQL Query:
WITH TopCategories AS (
    SELECT
        category_id,
        COUNT(*) AS film_count
    FROM film_category
    GROUP BY category_id
    ORDER BY film_count DESC
    LIMIT 5
),
HighReplacementCostFilms AS (
    SELECT
        f.film_id,
        f.title,
        f.replacement_cost
    FROM film f
    JOIN film_category fc ON f.film_id = fc.film_id
    JOIN TopCategories tc ON fc.category_id = tc.category_id
    ORDER BY f.replacement_cost DESC
)
SELECT *
FROM HighReplacementCostFilms;
Expected SQL Query:
WITH top_categories AS (
    SELECT 
        fc.category_id, 
        COUNT(r.rental_id) AS rental_count
    FROM 
        film_category fc
        JOIN inventory i ON fc.film_id = i.film_id
        JOIN rental r ON i.inventory_id = r.inventory_id
    GROUP BY 
        fc.category_id
    ORDER BY 
        rental_count DESC
    LIMIT 5
),
top_films AS (
    SELECT 
        f.film_id, 
        f.title, 
        f.replacement_cost, 
        c.name AS category_name
    FROM 
        film f
        JOIN film_category fc ON f.film_id = fc.film_id
        JOIN category c ON fc.category_id = c.category_id
        JOIN top_categories tc ON fc.category_id = tc.category_id
    ORDER BY 
        f.replacement_cost DESC
)
SELECT * FROM top_films;

Question: Can you find out which high-replacement-cost films are in the five most rented genres?

    SELECT
        category_id,
        COUNT(*) AS rental_count
    FROM
        film_category
    JOIN inventory ON film_category.film_id = inventory.film_id

        category_id
    ORDER BY
        rental_count DESC
    LIMIT 5
)

    f.replacement_cost DESC;

    GROUP BY

    ORDER BY

)

Question: Which two actors have appeared in the most movies together?
Generated SQL Query:
WITH actor_pairs AS (
    SELECT 
        fa1.actor_id AS actor1_id, 
        fa2.actor_id AS actor2_id, 
        COUNT(*) AS films_together
    FROM 
        film_actor fa1
        JOIN film_actor fa2 ON fa1.film_id = fa2.film_id
    WHERE 
        fa1.actor_id < fa2.actor_id
    GROUP BY 
        fa1.actor_id, fa2.actor_id
    ORDER BY 
        films_together DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT 
    a1.first_name AS actor1_first_name, 
    a1.last_name AS actor1_last_name, 
    a2.first_name AS actor2_first_name, 
    a2.last_name AS actor2_last_name
FROM 
    actor_pairs ap
    JOIN actor a1 ON ap.actor1_id = a1.actor_id
    JOIN actor a2 ON ap.actor2_id = a2.actor_id;

)

WHERE r.return_date <= (r.rental_date + INTERVAL '1 day' * f.rental_duration)
GROUP BY f.film_id, f.title
HAVING COUNT(r.rental_id) > 10;
